{
  "_about": "Curated registry of high-signal YouTube teachers, the primary source for ai-firehose.com. Eric edits this file. Each channel is polled via its free RSS feed: https://www.youtube.com/feeds/videos.xml?channel_id=<channel_id> (no API key).",
  "_instructions": "Prefer the CLI: node worker/sources/youtube_registry.mjs add @handle --weight=0.9 --kind=mixed (it resolves the channel_id and writes here idempotently). Full runbook: docs/ONBOARD_YOUTUBE_CHANNEL.md. To resolve a channel_id by hand, search the channel page source for \"channelId\" or run yt-dlp --print channel_id <channel_url>. authority_weight in [0,1] scales how strongly the channel moves the rotation: favorite, highest-signal teachers near 1.0. kind_bias is only a hint; the classifier decides each video's kind. Set active true to include a channel.",
